ep-412117314-359999101.html%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASmoky+Mountain+Opry+Theater\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Premiere-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Premiere_4-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Premiere_4-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Premiere_4-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">\"In Brief\". <i>Knoxville News Sentinel</i>. April 8, 2006. <q>The Miracle Theater in Sevierville (formerly the Louise Mandrell Theater) will open its headlining show \"The Miracle\" Thursday. \"The Miracle\" is an original musical production based on the life and miracles of Jesus Christ. The Fee Hedrick Family Entertainment Group, owners of Comedy Barn Theater and Black Bear Jamboree Theater, collaborated with the winning team of playwright Linda Nell Cooper and composer David Legg to produce the show.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Knoxville+News+Sentinel&amp;rft.atitle=In+Brief&amp;rft.date=2006-04-08&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASmoky+Mountain+Opry+Theater\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Hodges, Dereck (October 21, 2011). \"<span style=\"padding-left:0.2em;\">'</span>Miracle' nears final performance\". <i>The Mountain Press</i>. <q>\u201cThe Miracle\u201d has three more showings left, scheduled for 8 p.m. today and Saturday, and 3 p.m. Saturday. Fee says the possibilities for new life for \u201cMiracle\u201d include Christmas season matin\u00e9e shows at Smoky Mountain Opry, the name of both the theater and the new show it will host starting Nov. 4, and even the chance for a traveling production.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Mountain+Press&amp;rft.atitle=%27Miracle%27+nears+final+performance&amp;rft.date=2011-10-21&amp;rft.aulast=Hodges&amp;rft.aufirst=Dereck&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASmoky+Mountain+Opry+Theater\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Considine, Austin (January 15, 2009). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2009/01/16/travel/escapes/16rituals.html\">\"Gatlinburg, Tenn.: Return to Kitsch Mountain\"</a>. <i>The New York Times</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">April 6,</span> 2018</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+New+York+Times&amp;rft.atitle=Gatlinburg%2C+Tenn.%3A+Return+to+Kitsch+Mountain&amp;rft.date=2009-01-15&amp;rft.aulast=Considine&amp;rft.aufirst=Austin&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2009%2F01%2F16%2Ftravel%2Fescapes%2F16rituals.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASmoky+Mountain+Opry+Theater\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.pigeonforge.com/new-narrator-for-joseph-and-the-amazing-technicolor-dreamcoat/\">\"New Narrator for \"Joseph and the Amazing Technicolor Dreamcoat\" - PigeonForge.com\"</a>. <i>PigeonForge.com</i>. April 7, 2010<span class=\"reference-acc